@node Comments and suggestions (phase 2)
@section Comments and suggestions (phase 2)

This phase adds full collaboration support: comments, suggestions, and
live change awareness.  It will introduce a new module
@samp{gdocs-comments.el} and extend the sync and diff engines.

@menu
* Comments system::
* Suggesting mode::
* Periodic polling::
* Planned configuration variables (phase 2)::
@end menu

@node Comments system
@subsection Comments system

A side buffer (@code{gdocs-comments}) for viewing and managing Google Docs
comments.  The buffer will display in a side window (configurable via a
planned @code{gdocs-comments-side} option, defaulting to the right) and show
each comment with:

@itemize
@item
Author name and avatar (as text initials).
@item
Timestamp.
@item
The quoted text the comment is anchored to.
@item
Comment body.
@item
Reply thread (indented).
@item
Resolved status.
@end itemize

Comments will be linked to positions in the org buffer so that clicking
a comment in the side buffer jumps to the corresponding text.

Planned commands:

@itemize
@item
@code{gdocs-comments} — open or toggle the comments side buffer.
@item
@code{gdocs-comment-add} — select a region in the org buffer, then type a
comment.  Creates a comment anchored to that text in the Google Doc.
@item
@code{gdocs-comment-reply} — reply to the comment at point in the
comments buffer.
@item
@code{gdocs-comment-resolve} — resolve the comment at point.
@item
@code{gdocs-comment-delete} — delete the comment at point.
@end itemize

Comments will be fetched when pulling and when the comments buffer is
opened.  New comments created locally will be pushed immediately (on
comment creation, not on buffer save).

@node Suggesting mode
@subsection Suggesting mode

A new command @code{gdocs-suggesting-mode} will toggle between direct editing
and suggesting mode for the current buffer.  When suggesting mode is
active:

@itemize
@item
The modeline will show @samp{GDocs:suggesting}.
@item
On push, changes are sent as suggestions (using the Google Docs API's
@code{InsertText} / @code{DeleteContentRange} with @code{suggestedInsertionIds} /
@code{suggestedDeletionIds} fields) rather than direct edits.
@end itemize

When pulling, existing suggestions from other collaborators will be
displayed with distinct faces: green underline for suggested insertions,
strikethrough for suggested deletions.  Each suggestion will be
attributed to its author.

Planned commands for handling suggestions:

@itemize
@item
@code{gdocs-suggestion-accept} — accept the suggestion at point.
@item
@code{gdocs-suggestion-reject} — reject the suggestion at point.
@item
@code{gdocs-suggestion-accept-all} — accept all suggestions.
@item
@code{gdocs-suggestion-reject-all} — reject all suggestions.
@end itemize

@node Periodic polling
@subsection Periodic polling

When @code{gdocs-mode} is active, a timer will poll the Google Doc for
changes at a configurable interval (planned option:
@code{gdocs-poll-interval}, default 30 seconds).  Polling checks only the
document revision ID (a lightweight API call).

Behavior when remote changes are detected:

@itemize
@item
If the local buffer has no unsaved changes: auto-pull and update
silently, showing a brief message: ``Pulled remote changes.''
@item
If the local buffer has unsaved changes: show a warning in the
modeline (@samp{GDocs:conflict}) and notify: ``Remote changes detected.
Save to push your changes, or run @code{gdocs-pull} to pull.''
@end itemize

Polling will be paused while the buffer is in conflict resolution mode.
A command @code{gdocs-poll-toggle} will enable or disable polling per buffer.

