By default, the browser will show only Google Docs (filtered by MIME
type @samp{application/vnd.google-apps.document}).

@node Org export backend
@subsection Org export backend

A new module @samp{gdocs-export.el} will register as an org export backend
so that users can use the standard org export dispatcher.  The export
menu key will be @samp{g}, so the sequences are:

@itemize
@item
@samp{C-c C-e g d} — export to Google Docs (create new or update existing
linked Doc).
@item
@samp{C-c C-e g o} — export and open in browser.
@end itemize

The backend will parse the buffer with @code{org-element}, convert to Google
Docs API requests, and create or update the document.  For buffers
already linked to a Google Doc, this is equivalent to @code{gdocs-push}.
For unlinked buffers, it creates a new Google Doc and links the buffer.

